Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:00.367 --> 00:00:02.633
Narrator:
Welcome to the West Wing Week,
your guide to everything that's

00:00:02.633 --> 00:00:05.333
happening at 1600
Pennsylvania Avenue.

00:00:05.333 --> 00:00:08.066
This week, the President
addressed the national tragedy

00:00:08.066 --> 00:00:11.266
in Newtown, Connecticut, and
promised meaningful action to

00:00:11.266 --> 00:00:12.900
address gun violence.

00:00:12.900 --> 00:00:15.133
While the White House invited
some of its newest Pinterest

00:00:15.133 --> 00:00:18.934
followers and the President
spread some holiday cheer.

00:00:18.934 --> 00:00:21.166
That's December 14th
to December 20th,

00:00:21.166 --> 00:00:22.967
or "We Are There For Them."

00:00:25.734 --> 00:00:29.000
On Friday after the tragic
events in Newtown, Connecticut,

00:00:29.000 --> 00:00:31.200
the President delivered an
emotional statement in the

00:00:31.200 --> 00:00:32.166
White House briefing room.

00:00:34.900 --> 00:00:37.667
President Obama:
In the hard days to come, that
community needs us to be at our

00:00:37.667 --> 00:00:41.900
best as Americans, and I will
do everything in my power as

00:00:41.900 --> 00:00:43.433
President to help.

00:00:43.433 --> 00:00:48.367
All of us can extend a hand to
those in need to remind them

00:00:48.367 --> 00:00:54.567
that we are there for them, that
we are praying for them, that

00:00:54.567 --> 00:00:58.600
the love they felt for those
they lost endures not just in

00:00:58.600 --> 00:01:01.500
their memories,
but also in ours.

00:01:01.500 --> 00:01:04.700
Narrator:
On Sunday, the President
traveled to Newtown, Connecticut

00:01:04.700 --> 00:01:08.066
and spoke at an interfaith vigil
for the victims of the shooting

00:01:08.066 --> 00:01:08.667
and their families.

00:01:08.667 --> 00:01:11.667
President Obama:
We can't tolerate this anymore.

00:01:11.667 --> 00:01:14.433
These tragedies must end.

00:01:14.433 --> 00:01:16.433
And to end them, we must change.

